		<h2 class="centered">CliqBit™ Privacy Policy</h2>
		<p class="centered">Effective date: November 30th, 2015</p>
		<hr>
		<h3>What’s Up</h3>
		<p>CliqBit™ is a social platform to share humorous moments with other friends, followers, and groups or “Cliqs”. This Privacy Policy is intended to help you understand what data is generated from your CliqBit™ account and what is done with that information. When you post comments, pictures and video on CliqBit™, you agree that we are providing a platform that may be seen by others and where data will be collected by CliqBit™ consistent with the terms of this Privacy Policy and with our Terms of Service Policy, which can be found on this page and at this link: <a href="legal">https://cliqbitapp.com/legal</a></p>
		<br>
		<h3>Information We Collect</h3>
		<p>This is an overview detailing how CliqBit™ account information is used. There are three criteria of information:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>User identity information provided by you when you set up your user account</li>
			<li>Application usage information generated from your activity on CliqBit™</li>
			<li>Use of your information by third parties</li>
		</ul>
		<br>
		<h3>User Identity Information</h3>
		<p>The data you share with us when creating a CliqBit™ account such as a user name, password, identifying image, email address, and date of birth is information you provide when setting up your account. This information marks your identity on CliqBit™, ensures that you are a human being of appropriate age, and assists other users in finding you.</p>
		<p>CliqBit™ provides you with the option of choosing “Private Account” in your Account Settings. This feature allows your account to only be viewable by those following you, and in the future asks your permission before others may begin following your account and viewing your posts.</p>
		<br>
		<h3>Application usage information</h3>
		<p>As you utilize the different features of CliqBit™, you generate data on how you interact with the services and other users on CliqBit™. This information, such as usage frequency, “Cliqs” joined, and number of followers helps CliqBit™ to understand how the app is working, and where it may require some improvements or updates. </p>
		<p>To better understand CliqBit™ usage and to target new features, we identify your device type, operating system version and network connection. This specific device information is not linked to your account, but rather it is summarized for trending and analysis.</p>
		<p>The user content information you generate by using CliqBit™, such as pictures, videos, and posts are stored on our servers for a period of time. See “Information Storage” section for further information. </p>
		<p>CliqBit™ provides you with the option to “Share My Location” in your user settings. This allows CliqBit™ to offer location based features within the application, such as showing a map of where group posts come from. For safety reasons CliqBit™ will not disclose your specific location within the application without your permission. CliqBit™ may, at times, anonymize and aggregate your information into summary data by zip code, city, state or country.</p>
		<br>
		<h3>Use of your information by third parties</h3>
		<p>Third Parties may be used to gather data about your interaction with our service, to process transactions or to perform analyses of our services. We may share this information with such organizations as, (but not limited to) outside service providers and their affiliates, researchers, and legal entities (when pertinent or required). These third parties may be given your personal information needed to perform the services that CliqBit™ has engaged them to perform. These third party organizations will not be allowed to utilize your personal data for purposes other than to perform the services that they were engaged to provide.</p>
		<br>
		<h3>How We Use Information</h3>
		<p>Our main purpose in collecting information is to ensure CliqBit™ is fulfilling user needs and providing enhancements to keep our users smiling. Specifically, we:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Verify user identities and prevent unauthorized activities, security breaches or fraud</li>
			<li>Maintain and enhance the functionality of CliqBit™</li>
			<li>Analyze CliqBit™ usage and trends</li>
			<li>Communicate with and assist users</li>
		</ul>
		<p>We may also store some information locally on your device. For example, we may store information in a local cache so that you can open the app and view content faster. Storing certain information on your device locally improves the performance of the application and optimizes and limits data you must download to your device.</p>
		<p>In the event that CliqBit™ becomes part of another organization through a company merger or acquisition, your CliqBit™ user data may be transferred as part of that transaction.</p>
		<br>
		<h3>It’s On You</h3>
		<p>Information you share on CliqBit™ may be accessed by users who you designate can see your posts, whether it is in the main feed or within your 5 “Cliqs”. It’s important to be aware that any information shared online may be accessed by others. CliqBit™, LLC is not responsible for the actions of those who obtain the content that you have chosen to share.</p>
		<p>Please protect your account safety and your privacy by maintaining the secrecy of your account information and password at all times.</p>
		<br>
		<h3>Party Invites</h3>
		<p>You can choose to expand your “Cliqs” by “Inviting Friends to CliqBit™” from your Settings screen. When you choose “Find Friends to Follow” a message tells you that your contacts are periodically synced and stored on our servers. CliqBit™ provides you with the option to either choose “Ok”, or “Don’t Allow”. </p>
		<p>You may also invite friends to CliqBit™ by choosing the “Search” option within the service, and choosing “Connect With Facebook Friends”. Facebook is a third-party service and information provided to us from outside services is not governed by this Privacy Policy until it is received by CliqBit™.</p>
		<br>
		<h3>Information Storage</h3>
		<p>The CliqBit™ feature for disappearing feed allow pictures, videos and posts to move quickly. For the most part, messages sent through CliqBit™ servers will be deleted and/or written over at an undetermined period of time after the content has been set as either a 5 second or 48 hour post. The exception to this is when users choose a permanent feed.</p>
		<p>Keep in mind that CliqBit™ cannot guarantee that data will be deleted in a certain period of time. There are instances when data backup must adhere to certain legal guidelines, or when law enforcement requires an exception. As with any device, it’s important to know there are means to pull data off temporary storage on users’ devices, or to resurrect deleted information from a device.</p>
		<p>Finally, you can delete your account at any time. However, we may retain your account information for a reasonable time for audit, backup and archival reasons. Information that others have posted about you, and is not solely associated with your account, will not be deleted when your account is closed.</p>
		<br>
		<h3>Play Nice</h3>
		<p>CliqBit™, LLC reserves the right to disable your account if we detect that the property and safety of CliqBit™ or its users, is being abused.</p>
		<br>
		<h3>Getting Proofed </h3>
		<p>CliqBit™ is not intended for anyone under the age of 13. We will not collect any data from users who identify themselves as 12 and younger. </p>
		<br>
		<h3>Privacy Policy Changes</h3>
		<p>CliqBit™, LLC may update or modify this Privacy Policy without notifying you regarding pending changes and we encourage you to review it periodically. The “Effective Date” at the top of the Privacy Policy will indicate the most recent version of the Privacy Policy.</p>
